Sentencas: In the present paper the use of Ni infiltration into preformed porous yttria-stabilized zirconia structures is investigated as a possible solution to the redox problem of Ni-based solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) anodes and anode supports.
Titulo: Ni infiltration as a possible solution to the redox problem of SOFC anodes

Sentencas: It is shown that cermets containing 12-16 wt % Ni prepared by infiltration exhibited a conductivity above 300 S cm(-1) at room temperature, which dropped by 20% after one redox cycle, but was not accompanied by bulk dimensional changes.
Titulo: Ni infiltration as a possible solution to the redox problem of SOFC anodes

Sentencas: The dimensional stability is attributed to the properties of the microstructure that is produced by infiltration.
Titulo: Ni infiltration as a possible solution to the redox problem of SOFC anodes
